Obviously people are generally more caring, and the consequences of these semi-AI beings and their non-existent rights would cause quite a lot of Societal reflection, and people would probably question the integrity of the human ego and it's relation to our creation. Do we have a right to essentially enslave what is the equivalent of another sentient being? Or are they really just machines? Depends on who you are asking I suppose.
